@kalombos - this is similar to the option I suggested above - `queryset.filter('functionName(x, y, z)')`
Your implementation requires adding the `raw=` before the condition string, but it's possible to omit it by changing the implementation of `filter()` to accept strings as raw conditions.
This seems to be the simplest solution, but maybe not the most helpful solution for the user. Basically we're telling him "the ORM can't help you with this, you need to use raw SQL".

